, "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/TechEquityEng/status/2051473737040703936", "text": "\ud83d\udea8BREAKING \ud83d\udea8\n\nVolvo and $AUR just expanded their autonomous trucking network with a new commercial freight route to Oklahoma City.\n\nFrom the press release:\n\nThe route is part of Aurora\u2019s expanding driverless freight operations in the U.S.\n\n1) It builds on existing commercial lanes already running in Texas\n\n2) The trucks are Volvo autonomous vehicles powered by Aurora\u2019s self driving system\n\n3) Freight is being moved as part of real logistics operations, not a closed test program\n\nWhat this actually shows:\n\nAutonomous trucking is starting to stack into a connected network instead of isolated pilots.\n\nTexas corridors were the starting point\nNow the system is pushing outward into Oklahoma City\nEach expansion adds more real world routing complexity and volume\n\nLooks like $7 is coming faster than I thought. \ud83d\ude80\n\n-T.E.E.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 1, "replyCount": 1, "likeCount": 15, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 458, "createdAt": "Tue May 05 01:27:08 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 1, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2051473737040703936", "displayTextRange": [0, 274], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "TechEquityEng", "url": "https://x.com/TechEquityEng", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/TechEquityEng", "id": "1676251811974643712", "name": "Tech Equity Engineer", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2008764366989258756/81_7YwFo_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1676251811974643712/1777930543", "description": "", "location": "Silicon Valley", "followers": 815, "following": 197, "status": "", "canDm": false, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Tue Jul 04 15:29:24 +0000 2023", "entities": {"